{"text": "Thus if photons with a continuous range of frequencies pass through a rarefied gas and then are analysed with a spectrometer, a series of dark spectral absorption lines appear in the continuous spectrum.", "fibs": ["range"]}
{"text": "The dark lines indicate the frequencies that have been absorbed by the atoms of the gas.", "fibs": ["gas"]}
{"text": "The explanation of the hydrogen atom spectrum provided by Bohr’s model was a brilliant achievement, which greatly stimulated progress towards the modern quantum theory.", "fibs": ["explanation"]}
