{"text": "To explain the line spectra emitted by atoms, as well as the stability of atoms, Niel’s Bohr proposed a model for hydrogenic (single elctron) atoms.", "fibs": ["line"]}
{"text": "He introduced three postulates and laid the foundations of quantum mechanics:
	(a)	In a hydrogen atom, an electron revolves in certain stable orbits (called stationary orbits) without the emission of radiant energy.", "fibs": ["quantum"]}
{"text": "(b)	The stationary orbits are those for which the angular momentum is some integral multiple of h/2π.", "fibs": ["b"]}
